      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my blueberry bushes are turning kind of yellow on the leaves. i cant tell if they need more nitrogen or if the soil pH is just messed up. any idea how to tell the difference?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yellowing leaves on blueberry bushes can be a sign of several issues, but the color pattern often helps distinguish between nutrient deficiencies and pH problems. If the yellowing is uniform across older leaves, it might suggest a nitrogen issue, which is a common concern. However, if the yellowing is starting on the new growth or appears in specific patterns, it could point towards a pH imbalance affecting micronutrient uptake. Testing your soil specifically will give you the most accurate answer to know what your bushes truly need.",
