      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For a quick and easy check, a home soil test kit is a good starting point, especially if you want to see if the pH is drastically off. However, for the most reliable and professional results, submitting a soil sample to a local agricultural extension office or specialized lab is the best route. They can provide a comprehensive analysis that looks at pH, nitrogen levels, and other critical elements simultaneously. This detailed report will tell you exactly what amendments to use to correct the issue.",
